# .dockerignore — the build context filter for docker/Dockerfile.
#
# THIS FILE MUST LIVE AT THE REPO ROOT. docker/docker-compose.yml sets `context: ..`, and
# BuildKit reads <context>/.dockerignore. A copy placed next to the Dockerfile in docker/ is
# SILENTLY IGNORED — no warning, no error — and the first `COPY ReelScraper/ ./ReelScraper/`
# then bakes real creator video, reels_raw.json, every .env and platforms/x/session.txt into
# an immutable layer. `./cr build` asserts this file exists and that its first non-comment
# line is `**`, which is the cheap guard against someone "simplifying" it into a denylist.
#
# DENY EVERYTHING, THEN ALLOW. Not a denylist. The reason is checkable, not stylistic:
# ReelScraper/renders/, ReelScraper/studio/<platform>/, ReelScraper/evals/ and
# ReelScraper/discovery/ DO NOT EXIST on a fresh clone — the hub creates them the first time
# someone runs the pipeline. A denylist written today against the current tree omits them by
# inspection and starts leaking scraped data into image layers the moment a contributor
# builds after running ./demo. Deny-all-then-allow fails closed: a directory nobody has
# thought about yet is excluded until someone adds it here on purpose.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS MORE THAN USUAL HERE
#   Working tree today: ~546 MB.   `git ls-files`: ~320 files, ~3.4 MB.
#   A naive `COPY . .` would bake into an immutable layer:
#     ReelScraper/media/                     real Instagram video (mp4 + jpg per item)
#     platforms/instagram/reels_raw.json     scraped third-party content
#     AutoSearch/.env                        ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, IG_SESSIONID, IG_CSRFTOKEN
#     AnalysisEngine/.env, SimilarContent/.env   GEMINI_API_KEY
#     ReelScraper/platforms/x/session.txt    live X auth_token + ct0
#     .git/                                  the whole history, incl. any .env ever committed
#   Deleting them in a later RUN does not remove them from the image.
#
# THIS FILE IS THE BELT, NOT THE BRACES.
#   Release images are built from a clean git export, never from a working tree:
#       git archive HEAD | docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t cuttingroom:<tag> -
#   because .dockerignore cannot express "the COMMITTED version of this tracked file", and
#   ReelScraper/memory/<platform>/patterns.md and MEMORY.md are git-tracked AND agent-mutated
#   — `clean` restores them from git precisely because after real work they hold observations
#   about real analyzed reels. A build from a working checkout bakes the mutated versions.
#   Those two files are deliberately NOT excluded below: the agents read them, and the git
#   export is what makes their content safe.

# ---- deny everything --------------------------------------------------------------------
**

# ---- allow the four uv projects and the shared trees ------------------------------------
# Both forms per tree: `!X` keeps the directory walkable, `!X/**` keeps its contents.
!ReelScraper
!ReelScraper/**
!AnalysisEngine
!AnalysisEngine/**
!AutoSearch
!AutoSearch/**
!SimilarContent
!SimilarContent/**
!_producer-template
!_producer-template/**
!Dashboard
!Dashboard/**
!documentation
!documentation/**
!scripts
!scripts/**
!niches
!niches/**
!demo-data
!demo-data/**

# ---- allow the bash entry points ---------------------------------------------------------
# COPY'd into the `dev` target only, but they must be IN the context for that COPY to work.
# `cr` is deliberately absent: it is a host-side launcher and has no job inside an image.
!init
!demo
!stop
!clean
!health
!docsite

# ---- allow the container files -----------------------------------------------------------
!docker
!docker/**

# ==========================================================================================
# RE-EXCLUDE, inside the allowed trees. Last match wins, so everything below overrides the
# `!` rules above.
# ==========================================================================================

# ---- secrets. Never in a layer, never in a volume. ---------------------------------------
# The hub reads agent .env files for PRESENCE ONLY (app.py:614 — "never returned, never
# logged"), and app.py ORs the hub's live environment with the agent's .env, so env-only
# injection already reads as "present" in the Dashboard with zero source change. The bind
# mount delivers the real files at runtime; the image must never carry them.
# `.env.example` files ARE tracked and ARE wanted — the patterns below do not match them.
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local
**/session.txt
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/credentials.json

# ---- build and dependency output ---------------------------------------------------------
# Also a CORRECTNESS requirement, not just size. app.py:333-337 `_interpreter()` returns
# ROOT/.venv/bin/python IF IT EXISTS — it checks existence, never architecture. A macOS
# Mach-O .venv/bin/python copied into a Linux image becomes PY, and every scrape/analyze/
# media stage then dies with OSError: [Errno 8] Exec format error, recorded as rc -1
# (app.py:2214), from a container that started perfectly.
**/.venv/
**/venv/
**/node_modules/
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/*.pyo
**/.pytest_cache/
**/*.egg-info/
**/.ruff_cache/
**/.mypy_cache/
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov/
Dashboard/dist/
ReelScraper/frontend/dist/
documentation/site/

# ---- real scraped third-party content ----------------------------------------------------
# Publishing this is treated as a serious violation here (the anchored "live working data"
# block in .gitignore; demo prints a warning; demo-data/README.md).
ReelScraper/media/
ReelScraper/renders/
ReelScraper/analysis/
ReelScraper/studio/*/
ReelScraper/evals/
ReelScraper/discovery/
ReelScraper/producers/
ReelScraper/references/
ReelScraper/backups/
ReelScraper/platforms/*/content.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/profiles_meta.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*_raw*.json
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*.csv
ReelScraper/platforms/*/*.xlsx
# Hand-curated real creator targeting lists — unreproducible operator input AND real handles.
ReelScraper/platforms/*/pages.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/creators.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/seeds.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/keywords.txt
ReelScraper/platforms/*/discovered_pages.txt

# ---- agent-local state and operator scratch ----------------------------------------------
# pipeline_cascade.json is new (the percentage funnel, app.py:2791) and holds this operator's
# tuned batch size, pass-through percentages and per-stage marks. pipeline_schedule.json
# (app.py:2635) holds their schedule. config/agents/*.json holds per-agent config including
# the `discovery_enabled` kill switch. None of that is anyone else's default.
ReelScraper/memory/*/content.db
ReelScraper/memory/shared/insights.jsonl
ReelScraper/memory/shared/INSIGHTS.md
ReelScraper/config/agents/
ReelScraper/config/pipeline_schedule.json
ReelScraper/config/pipeline_cascade.json
AnalysisEngine/work/
AutoSearch/memory/plan.json
AutoSearch/memory/caps/
AutoSearch/*_raw.json
SimilarContent/assets/

# ---- LOGS ARE THIRD-PARTY-IDENTIFYING, not diagnostics -----------------------------------
# ReelScraper/logs/agents.jsonl carries a content_id per record; media filenames are
# <media_pk>_<user_pk> and the trailing field is a real account PK. Scrape logs additionally
# embed absolute host paths (/Users/<name>/...).
**/logs/
.hub.log
.hub.pid

# ---- the demo dataset travels privately and never in an image ----------------------------
# `**/*.zip` costs nothing: no tracked file in this repo is a .zip, and `clean` writes its
# archives to backups/, excluded below.
**/*.zip
demodataset.zip
demo-data/manifest.json
demo-data/data/**
!demo-data/data/.gitkeep

# ---- archives of real data. The single densest leak vector: one file, every scraped
#      artifact, no keys but the whole corpus.
backups/

# ---- history and CI ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.github/
.pre-commit-config.yaml

# ---- noise -------------------------------------------------------------------------------
**/.DS_Store
**/*.swp
**/*.swo
**/.idea/
**/.vscode/
**/.claude/
**/.playwright-mcp/
